Cloud smoke — make smoke-live-cloud
================================================================================
Duration: 42s before failure.
Status: RED — runner registration failed, destroy reported pending despite cascade.

PASSES:
  ✓ Empty-project precheck OK (D-12 gate 1 PASS)
  ✓ runnerkit up provisioned 5 Hetzner resources (server, ssh-key, firewall,
    primary-ipv4, primary-ipv6) cleanly
  ✓ Cleanup trap fired correctly on failure → automatic destroy attempt
  ✓ Hetzner project ended empty (verified post-test) — auto_delete cascade
    DID work to clean up primary IPs, despite destroy reporting pending.
    Plan 06-11 Bug 26's cascade approach works in practice.

FAILURE — Bug 29 (NEW):
  runnerkit up --cloud hetzner exited 255 after 42s with:
    "ERROR Cloud machine is not ready for runner registration yet.
     Fix the provider or SSH readiness issue, then rerun runnerkit up..."

  42s is too short for Hetzner cloud-init (typically 60-120s). The cloud-up
  SSH-readiness check needs a longer poll/backoff before declaring failure,
  OR a documented retry pattern that the smoke harness honors.

FAILURE — Bug 30 (NEW):
  runnerkit destroy --yes (via trap) reported:
    • provider_server: done
    • provider_primary_ip: pending Primary IP must be unassigned
      (must_be_unassigned, be1e2b9c6cf6161e3693f448ee1df45f)
    • provider_primary_ip: pending Primary IP must be unassigned
      (must_be_unassigned, 8e24699cb8fb14adcbf58be364793175)
    • provider_firewall: done
    • RKD-PROV-006 emitted

  Race between server.Delete (returns synchronously but cascade is async) and
  the explicit DeletePrimaryIP calls at internal/provider/hetzner/destroy.go:95-96.
  The cascade eventually deletes the IPs (verified empty afterward), but the
  destroy command reports pending and exits non-zero — the smoke trap surfaces
  RKD-PROV-006 and the verifier can't pass.

  Plan 06-11 Bug 26 comments state "explicit DeletePrimaryIP calls now race
  against the cascade (Hetzner returns 404 once the cascade completes; our
  isAlreadyAbsentError already treats 404 as a no-op)" — but in practice
  Hetzner returns "must_be_unassigned" (HTTP 409 conflict), NOT 404, while the
  cascade is still in flight. isAlreadyAbsentError doesn't match 409.

  Fix shape: skip explicit DeletePrimaryIP entirely when AutoDelete=true was
  recorded in state at provision time, OR treat must_be_unassigned as a
  transient error and retry/poll until 404, OR power off server before
  delete + unassign + delete (Plan 06-11 rejected this for the cascade
  approach).

